<p>I have a problem with Infinitest:</p>  <p>I'm working with a junit temporary folder :</p>  <pre><code>@Rule public TemporaryFolder testFolder = new TemporaryFolder(); </code></pre>  <p>then I'm trying in the test method to create a temp sub-folder in this temp folder, and work with it :</p>  <pre><code>@Test public void shouldCheckFolders() throws InputDataException, IOException {     File subFolder = testFolder.newFolder("subFolder");      // ... anything for the test } </code></pre>  <p>When running the test using maven Clean install, no problem, I have a success. When using Eclipse : Run As -> Junit test, no problem : everything is green.</p>  <p>But Infinitest has an error :</p>  <pre><code>NoSuchMethodError (org.junit.rules.TemporaryFolder.newFolder(Ljava/lang/String;)Ljava/io/File;) in LeTest.shouldCheckFolders     </code></pre>  <p>Any idea ?  is it possible to work with temporary folder and InfiniTest ?</p>  <p>I'm using Spring Tool Suite, based on Eclipse Mars 4.5.0 with Infinitest 5.1 and Junit 4.10.</p>